11:25.168 --> 11:26.259
♪<i> Whoo-ooh,</i>
<i> yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.</i> ♪

11:26.353 --> 11:28.186
And Daedalus tells Icarus,

11:28.337 --> 11:29.354
"Hey, buddy, don't fly

11:29.505 --> 11:31.172
"too high or the sun
will melt the wax

11:31.266 --> 11:34.008
on your wings, and you'll fall."
But Icarus gets pretty cocky,

11:34.102 --> 11:37.344
and he flies way up in the sky,
and sure enough,

11:37.364 --> 11:40.924
wax melts,
and Icarus comes tumbling down.

11:41.092 --> 11:42.942
I can't relate
to this story at all.

11:43.094 --> 11:45.870
Icarus? More like
"Dumb as a stick-arus."

11:46.097 --> 11:47.947
Let's open that marketplace.

11:48.099 --> 11:50.024
I know that the windup dolphin
costs a lot,

11:50.101 --> 11:51.192
but I have the coins,

11:51.211 --> 11:53.545
and it sure would look
badass in my tub.

11:53.772 --> 11:55.955
Bup, bup, bup. Lower shelf only.

11:56.107 --> 11:57.607
-Hello, you.
-Rudy.

11:57.625 --> 11:59.533
Ooh, I hadn't even noticed
that laser pointer.

11:59.553 --> 12:01.277
-Millie.
-MS. PADARO: What can I get

12:01.446 --> 12:02.628
-for you, Rudy?
-Uh...

12:02.723 --> 12:04.538
Three bouncy balls.
That's all we're getting.

12:04.632 --> 12:07.508
-One for each of us. Thank you.
-(Millie and Rudy groan)

12:08.544 --> 12:11.545
This is a magical
basement wonderland.

12:11.639 --> 12:14.640
♪<i> I haven't had</i>
<i> a space of my own</i> ♪

12:14.793 --> 12:16.609
♪<i> Since I was a kid</i> ♪

12:18.221 --> 12:21.072
♪<i> Who knew I could decorate</i> ♪

12:21.224 --> 12:22.982
♪<i> Like I just did?</i> ♪

12:24.077 --> 12:28.062
♪<i> Down here,</i>
<i> it could be Christmas</i> ♪

12:28.081 --> 12:29.581
♪<i> Or summer</i> ♪

12:29.808 --> 12:31.140
♪<i> Donna Summer</i> ♪

12:31.159 --> 12:34.711
♪<i> 'Cause bedtime is me time</i> ♪

12:37.165 --> 12:39.382
♪<i> I love Mom,</i>
<i> but I need a break</i> ♪

12:40.668 --> 12:43.911
♪<i> It's a school night,</i>
<i> for frick's sake</i> ♪

12:43.930 --> 12:47.323
TINA and GENE:
♪<i> Bedtime is me time</i> ♪

12:47.416 --> 12:50.435
ALL:
♪<i> Bedtime is me time</i> ♪

12:50.512 --> 12:53.104
♪<i> Not one bedside table,</i>
<i> but two</i> ♪

12:53.331 --> 12:56.590
♪<i> A book I'm almost</i>
<i> a quarter way through</i> ♪

12:56.684 --> 13:00.186
♪<i> And that's not even</i>
<i> the best part</i> ♪

13:00.338 --> 13:03.281
♪<i> A bathroom of my own</i> ♪

13:03.432 --> 13:05.174
♪<i> I poop like a king</i> ♪

13:05.193 --> 13:08.344
♪<i> A candle, lemon water</i> ♪

13:08.363 --> 13:11.605
♪<i> I heard that's a thing</i> ♪

13:11.625 --> 13:13.182
(sustains note)

13:13.201 --> 13:16.628
♪<i> 'Cause bedtime is me time</i> ♪

13:16.779 --> 13:20.373
ALL:
♪<i> Bedtime is me time.</i> ♪

13:20.525 --> 13:21.524
(lamp clicks)

13:21.543 --> 13:24.027
Hey, uh, how you doing
today, buddy?

13:24.045 --> 13:25.970
I was a little worried
about you yesterday.

13:26.197 --> 13:27.713
Oh, what,
with the dolphin? Pfft.

13:27.808 --> 13:29.641
I didn't cry about it
in the bathtub at all.

13:29.868 --> 13:31.551
Hey, friends.
Look who was feeling

13:31.645 --> 13:33.294
a little crafty last night.

13:33.371 --> 13:35.146
-RUDY: Whoa.
-LOUISE: What are you doing?

13:35.298 --> 13:37.557
We have a system.
We have quality control.

13:37.651 --> 13:39.967
You can't just make
more coins on your own.

13:39.986 --> 13:42.153
-Oh, but I did.
-Wow. No offense,

13:42.305 --> 13:43.804
but some of these
are really bad.

13:43.898 --> 13:46.640
Oh, no! Some coins aren't
the exact right perfect shape.

13:46.660 --> 13:47.567
Sue me.

13:47.661 --> 13:49.160
Millie, that one's
basically square.

13:49.312 --> 13:50.995
And I'm pretty sure
that's a penny.

13:51.147 --> 13:52.646
Okay, God!

13:52.666 --> 13:54.057
I won't use the really bad ones.

13:54.150 --> 13:56.317
That's all of them.
Okay, new rule, Millie,

13:56.411 --> 13:57.818
no using any of those coins.

13:57.912 --> 14:00.913
I didn't realize today was
bring your mother to school day.

14:01.066 --> 14:04.676
-You guys coming in?
-Yup. Get me
to the Greek, right?

14:06.905 --> 14:08.847
Whoa!

14:08.998 --> 14:10.348
(phone chimes)

14:10.425 --> 14:13.334
"Did you know peppercorns
are actually dried berries?"

14:13.353 --> 14:15.169
Aw. He loves that pepper book.

14:15.263 --> 14:17.246
"You're cute
when you read a book."

14:17.265 --> 14:18.414
Hey, if you want
to chat with Dad,

14:18.433 --> 14:19.932
I could rest my eyes
for a few hours.

14:20.026 --> 14:22.085
Yeah, I think I left
the Dutch oven on in my bed.

14:22.178 --> 14:23.361
I should go check it.

14:23.530 --> 14:26.013
No, no, no. Sorry, I'm off.
We're moisturizing.

14:26.032 --> 14:27.848
-Okay, sure.
-Great.

14:27.868 --> 14:29.275
-(phone chimes)
-Wait, hold on.

14:29.427 --> 14:31.536
"I think I might need
reading glasses."

14:31.763 --> 14:34.021
"Get them. You'll look good.

14:34.115 --> 14:36.449
Like a sexy senior citizen."

14:36.618 --> 14:38.859
Yup. I-I need glasses.

14:38.953 --> 14:42.213
The Hippocratic Oath
is named after...

14:42.365 --> 14:44.440
Oops. Did anyone
drop a coin? Huh.

14:44.533 --> 14:46.275
-This one looks
a little different.
-Millie.

14:46.294 --> 14:49.112
-What the hell?
-Uh, different how?

14:49.205 --> 14:51.538
-The shape's a little funny.
-Like "ha-ha" funny?

14:51.633 --> 14:54.617
I mean, it's-- not like
it's counterfeit. (chuckles)

14:54.710 --> 14:56.227
Yeah. No one would do that.

14:56.304 --> 14:58.287
And if it was, I did put in

14:58.289 --> 15:00.214
a little secret
security feature.

15:00.233 --> 15:03.550
Security feature? That sounds,
uh, neat. What is that?

15:03.570 --> 15:06.070
When I made my coins,
I baked in a little strip

15:06.297 --> 15:08.981
of aluminum foil,
so I'd know they were mine. See?

15:09.075 --> 15:10.408
Oh. There's no foil.

15:10.577 --> 15:12.535
That's weird. Huh...

15:13.729 --> 15:15.396
Foil.

15:15.415 --> 15:17.898
No foil. Foil.

15:17.992 --> 15:19.825
Foil. No foil.

15:19.978 --> 15:21.978
Wait, someone's making
fake coins?

15:22.071 --> 15:24.088
-Looks like it.
-Isn't that, like, bad?

15:24.315 --> 15:25.665
Yes. It's really bad.

15:25.741 --> 15:27.425
Should we call the FBI?

15:27.652 --> 15:29.485
Maybe. No, probably not.

15:29.487 --> 15:31.763
But I want whoever did this
to step forward.

15:31.914 --> 15:33.264
All right.

15:33.416 --> 15:35.099
I'll let the guilty party
sleep on it,

15:35.251 --> 15:38.252
and if no one comes forward
tomorrow, then no symposium.

15:38.271 --> 15:40.012
-No what?
-No party.

15:40.106 --> 15:41.347
-(all exclaiming)
-My heart!

15:41.499 --> 15:42.999
But what about
the bottomless grape juice?

15:43.092 --> 15:46.093
-Gone.
-What about the baklava
for days?

15:46.171 --> 15:47.353
Bakla-not gonna happen.

15:47.522 --> 15:49.530
-Aw, man.
-(others groaning)
-Oh, crap.

15:53.787 --> 15:55.511
I got to say,
I miss the cushions.

15:55.604 --> 15:57.271
Yeah, is it okay to sit on
the couch's skeleton like this?

15:57.365 --> 15:58.681
If you saw my setup
in the basement,

15:58.774 --> 16:00.866
you'd agree it's worth it,
but also, let me know

16:01.019 --> 16:02.943
-if you have any blankets
you're not using.
-(phone rings)

16:02.963 --> 16:05.296
Hello? Oh, hi, Rudy. Louise,

16:05.448 --> 16:08.024
-it's for you.
-Um, I'll take it
in the kitchen.

16:08.193 --> 16:10.209
Got it. Hello?

16:10.361 --> 16:12.303
Hey, Louise. It's Rudy.
Quick question.

16:12.530 --> 16:14.380
Do you think they'll let me
take my stuffed animal to jail

16:14.474 --> 16:16.474
because I can't sleep
without Pancake!

16:16.625 --> 16:18.309
No one's going
to jail, okay, buddy?

16:18.461 --> 16:20.294
Hold on, that's the other line.

16:20.313 --> 16:21.871
-I don't think I would like
the food there.
-Hello?

16:21.964 --> 16:23.723
I think we got to get rid of
Rudy. I think he's gonna talk.

16:23.850 --> 16:25.316
Millie, he's not
gonna talk, okay?

16:25.485 --> 16:27.819
He's on the other line, and he's
cool as a cucumber. Hold on.

16:28.046 --> 16:29.970
-Rudy, how we doing?
-I'm freaking out!

16:30.048 --> 16:31.214
Hold on. Hi, Millie.

16:31.232 --> 16:32.973
How's Rudy?
He's cracking, right?

16:33.051 --> 16:34.509
He's slightly worried.

16:34.511 --> 16:36.828
He, you know, doesn't want
to ruin the party for everyone.

16:37.055 --> 16:38.237
People can get grape juice

16:38.331 --> 16:40.072
other places in their life,
Louise, it's fine.

16:40.225 --> 16:41.240
Hey, I'm not worried about it,

16:41.334 --> 16:43.167
or feeling guilty
about it, at all.

16:43.319 --> 16:45.336
You're not gonna make a peep.
Rudy's not gonna make a peep.

16:45.488 --> 16:46.896
Anyone who makes a peep
gets hit in the head

16:46.989 --> 16:49.156
-with a lead peep.
-Okay, okay, geez.

16:49.250 --> 16:51.158
You still back there, sweetie?

16:51.252 --> 16:52.677
Oh, sorry.
I might've fallen asleep

16:52.846 --> 16:55.404
-from all the fun we're having.
-You should do what I do,

16:55.423 --> 16:57.515
-use your face as a hand.
-(phone rings)

16:57.742 --> 16:59.350
-Hi, hon.
-Hey, Lin. What-what
are you up to?

16:59.577 --> 17:02.002
Little back rub train
before bed. What about you?

17:02.096 --> 17:04.247
I was just about to go to sleep,
but I thought,

17:04.265 --> 17:05.748
you know, I'd say good night.

17:05.767 --> 17:08.084
Mm. Boy, I just realized
I-I haven't had

17:08.086 --> 17:09.752
my toothbrush in a long time.

17:09.771 --> 17:12.196
Oh, I noticed. Hey, I could
bring it down for you.

17:12.348 --> 17:14.181
You-you want to come here? Now?

17:14.200 --> 17:15.608
Yeah, I want to see
what you've done down there.

17:15.760 --> 17:19.037
Okay. Uh, great. I'll-I'll
see you in a few minutes.

17:19.188 --> 17:21.205
Oh, my God, Linda's coming over.

17:21.357 --> 17:23.266
This place is not ready
for company.

17:23.284 --> 17:26.360
Too sad. Too Dixieland-y.
Here we go.

17:26.454 --> 17:28.028
-(soft music playing)
-LINDA: Knock, knock.

17:28.197 --> 17:30.364
Ooh, it's nice down here.

17:30.458 --> 17:32.608
Look at you with the lights
and the stuff.

17:32.701 --> 17:35.278
I feel like I'm in
a dirty basement in Paris.

17:35.296 --> 17:36.445
(grunts) Ooh, it's cold, though.

17:36.464 --> 17:38.464
Yeah, it can get
a little chilly.

17:38.616 --> 17:40.207
I've been sleeping with all
the blankets I could find

17:40.226 --> 17:41.375
and three towels.

17:41.394 --> 17:43.302
-Here's your toothbrush.
-Thank you.

17:43.454 --> 17:45.730
I'll put that... here.
Would you like a drink?

17:45.915 --> 17:47.714
I'm making myself
a beer in a glass.

17:47.734 --> 17:50.902
Fancy. I'll take a wine
in a glass, if you have one,

17:50.978 --> 17:52.478
and I don't want to be forward,
but I might

17:52.630 --> 17:54.480
get in your bed real quick
'cause it's freezing.

17:54.632 --> 17:57.817
How about wine that's a beer?
And we share the glass.

17:57.893 --> 17:59.485
And it's not cold.

17:59.637 --> 18:02.655
Everything else here is cold,
but the beer is warm.

18:02.807 --> 18:04.916
-Let's see if I can... (groans)
-Oh. Okay.

18:05.067 --> 18:06.492
-All right.
-...squeeze in here. I'm in.

18:06.644 --> 18:07.977
-Oh! It's tight.
-We're both, we're both in.

18:07.995 --> 18:09.570
-I'm off! Now I'm off.
-We're both in. Oh!

18:09.664 --> 18:11.647
-Now I'm off.
-Let me, let me
pull you back up.

18:11.649 --> 18:13.816
I can be off, uh, over here
a little bit. It's fine.

18:13.835 --> 18:15.301
This is nice.

18:16.262 --> 18:17.411
I should come back
upstairs, right?

18:17.505 --> 18:19.580
Yeah, you should.
I miss your night farts.

18:19.599 --> 18:22.249
It's always three in a row.
It's comforting.

18:22.268 --> 18:24.343
Yeah, and I miss hearing
your sleep muttering.

18:24.495 --> 18:26.753
Whatever it is you're saying,
you're very emphatic.

18:26.848 --> 18:29.273
I'm not kicking anymore,
by the way. The kids are.

18:29.425 --> 18:30.775
They're kicking me like crazy.

18:30.960 --> 18:32.335
I guess they started
fighting back.

18:32.428 --> 18:33.927
Should I, uh,
bring the Christmas lights?

18:33.947 --> 18:36.005
Yeah, and the beer,
and brush your teeth.

18:36.023 --> 18:37.356
Right, right.

18:37.508 --> 18:38.783
<i> MS. PADARO:</i>
<i> Okay, everyone.</i>

18:38.934 --> 18:40.601
You had a night
to think about it.

18:40.620 --> 18:43.012
Who wants to come forward?

18:43.147 --> 18:44.513
Well, then, unfortunately,

18:44.532 --> 18:46.290
I have to call off
the symposium.

18:46.442 --> 18:48.108
-(students groan)
-Come on!
-Just say you did it,

18:48.128 --> 18:49.794
whoever you are.
I deserve a party.

18:49.963 --> 18:51.537
I haven't been to one
since Saturday.

18:51.631 --> 18:53.614
Yeah, and I'm not allowed
to have grape juice at home,

18:53.708 --> 18:54.857
so fess up!

18:54.950 --> 18:57.284
You know, I'm just--
I'm really disappointed,

18:57.362 --> 18:58.469
and the ancient Greeks
would be, too.

18:58.638 --> 19:01.547
They believed in ethics,
fairness, justice.

19:01.699 --> 19:02.974
I mean, to be honest,

19:03.125 --> 19:04.884
I don't know if I want to do
this unit again.

19:04.978 --> 19:07.036
-What do you mean?
-It's a lot of work. I mean,

19:07.054 --> 19:08.888
I buy all this stuff
with my own money.

19:09.040 --> 19:11.223
It's too much if something
like this is gonna happen.

19:11.376 --> 19:14.318
Oh, uh, well, philosophically,

19:14.470 --> 19:16.379
maybe we should
talk this through.

19:16.472 --> 19:18.472
That-That's Greek, right?
Philosophically?

19:18.566 --> 19:21.159
-Yeah.
-Well, speaking of fairness,

19:21.310 --> 19:23.402
whoever made the coins,
I'm just guessing,

19:23.554 --> 19:25.830
maybe they did it
because it wasn't quite fair

19:26.057 --> 19:27.665
the way the coins
were being handed out.

19:27.892 --> 19:29.909
I'm just using
the Socratic method.

19:30.003 --> 19:31.243
That's not the Socratic method.

19:31.396 --> 19:33.504
Uh, is it not
the Socratic method?

19:33.731 --> 19:35.064
That's the Socratic method.

19:35.082 --> 19:36.565
Oh, really? I'm just saying,

19:36.584 --> 19:40.178
I don't know, but I'm imagining
that, whoever did this,

19:40.329 --> 19:42.013
they might have had
their hand up a lot

19:42.164 --> 19:44.331
and didn't get called on
because sitting in a circle

19:44.350 --> 19:46.517
is not a great idea
because it's a bad idea.

19:46.744 --> 19:48.335
I mean, is it not a bad idea?

19:48.429 --> 19:51.004
So, hypothetically,
this person felt

19:51.082 --> 19:53.858
it was okay for them
to make fake coins?

19:54.009 --> 19:56.360
You know, Socrates said
suffering an injustice

19:56.512 --> 19:59.012
does not make it okay
to commit an injustice.

19:59.032 --> 20:00.364
Good to know, good to know.

20:00.516 --> 20:02.758
Um, maybe the people
who committed the injustice

20:02.777 --> 20:05.536
also feel bad about getting
the party canceled

20:05.613 --> 20:07.446
and also kind of
really liked the class

20:07.598 --> 20:10.208
and maybe wouldn't want you
to stop teaching it.

20:10.435 --> 20:12.359
And maybe those people
didn't sleep at all last night,

20:12.437 --> 20:14.119
even though they have Pancake.

20:14.272 --> 20:15.529
I don't know, maybe
those people don't feel

20:15.623 --> 20:17.882
any regret at all, just
adrenaline, and that's fine.

20:18.033 --> 20:21.126
Hmm. I guess the rewards thing
can be problematic.

20:21.279 --> 20:22.720
Also, at any given moment,
I can't see

20:22.947 --> 20:25.038
half the class,
and I'm nearsighted,

20:25.058 --> 20:26.724
and my hearing's not that great.

20:26.875 --> 20:28.893
Maybe this is more ethically
complicated than I thought.

20:29.044 --> 20:30.377
I'm not sure what's happening,

20:30.396 --> 20:31.395
but does that mean
we can have the party?

20:31.622 --> 20:34.047
-Uh, yeah. Okay.
-(students cheer)

20:34.067 --> 20:35.215
I guess we should accept

20:35.384 --> 20:36.734
that we may never
get to the bottom of this.

20:36.961 --> 20:39.962
Louise, Rudy, Millie, will you
see me after class? No reason.

20:39.981 --> 20:41.054
Yup. Yup. Yup.

20:41.074 --> 20:42.815
-Oh, God.
-Not a peep.

20:42.909 --> 20:44.984
-(music playing)
-(overlapping chatter)

20:45.152 --> 20:46.577
I got it, I got it.

20:46.729 --> 20:49.062
Third time you bumped the table.
(chuckles) Just saying,

20:49.156 --> 20:50.581
but, uh, have fun.

20:50.733 --> 20:52.825
Totally fair punishment,
Ms. Padaro.

20:52.994 --> 20:54.143
-Yup.
-I know.

20:54.161 --> 20:55.419
Hey, so my dad
has a laser printer.

20:55.571 --> 20:58.422
-I think we can make $30 bills.
-Bad influence!

20:58.574 --> 20:59.498
<i> Bad influence!</i>

20:59.650 --> 21:01.074
Pancake, my number one

21:01.094 --> 21:03.486
snuggle pal, this is for you.

21:03.504 --> 21:07.098
♪<i> Your eyes are on the same</i>
